java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.RootPaneContainer, javax.swing.WindowConstants
public class HangmanClient
extends javax.swing.JFrame

This class is the GUI class of the Hangman game. It handles all the GUI components, the control flow flow via button events and initializes the connection to the server.

gameInputSetEnabled

private void gameInputSetEnabled(java.lang.Boolean enabled)
This method enables or disables all the inputs for a game. These are the letter and word input and the letter and word try buttons and the new game. It also clears the user inputs if they are becoming enabled.

Parameters:
enabled - true to enable, false to disable

setGameStarted

public void setGameStarted(java.lang.String word,
                           int numOfAttempts,
                           int score)
Initializes the GUI when a new game starts.

Parameters:
score - the current score of the player
numOfAttempts - the remaining number of attempts for this game
word - the target word

setCharacterPlayed

public void setCharacterPlayed(java.lang.String word,
                               int numOfAttempts,
                               java.lang.Character c,
                               boolean correctLetter)
This method updates the GUI of the user in order to facilitate a correct or not character try. It updates the word, the tries left, the message to the user and the incorrect characters played so far.

Parameters:
word - the changed (or not) word
numOfAttempts - how many attempts the user still have
c - the character that user played, and as a response this method is call
correctLetter - boolean that indicates if the letter was correct or not

setPlayerWonOrLost

public void setPlayerWonOrLost(java.lang.Boolean won,
                               java.lang.String word,

Parameters:
won - boolean that indicates if won or lost
word - the target word
score - the updated score

setConnectionLost

public void setConnectionLost()
This method handles the case that the connection (socket) with the server was lost. The user is informed, everything is reinitializes and the user can try to reconnect to a server.

setCommunicationError

public void setCommunicationError(boolean newGameTry)
This method handles the errors that are not due to socket close.

Parameters:
newGameTry - if the error occurred while the user were trying to establish a new game
